result.execSummary:
The defendant Bradley Kenneth Warwick was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Operating Commercial Motor Vehicle without a License - WI Resident, an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 343.05(2)(a)1.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Costs to be paid directly to the Waushara County Clerk of Court within 60 days or establish a payment plan.  Failure to pay may result in suspension of your driver's license, tax intercept, a civil judgment being entered against you, a warrant being issued for your arrest for contempt and/or the debt being turned over to a collection agency.
DNA sample to be provided and surcharge assessed.

records.addlTxt: 1:15 pm case called. Defendant Bradley Kenneth Warwick in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Agreement reached and stated on the record.   Defendant advised of right to counsel and expertise.  Voluntary waiver of counsel accepted by Court.  Defendant advised of minimum/maximum penalty.  Plea colloquy entertained.  Collateral consequences explained. Chapter 950 compliance addressed. Plea: Guilty. Court accepts plea and enters JOC. Court sentences the defendant to: Costs to be paid within 60 days or payment plan. DNA sample to be given. Appeal Rights Given.

NOT PUT OF RECORD (2:47 PM): Defendant Bradley Kenneth Warwick not in court.  Scott Blader appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Per DA:  Believes that Def may still be trying to obtain CDL.   State does not request warrant at this time.  P/S Scheduled for mandatory appearance.  Plea/sentencing hearing scheduled for October 13, 2015 at 01:15 pm.

Case called @ 3:02 p.m. Defendant Bradley Kenneth Warwick in court.  Steven Paul Anderson appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Complaint Stated - Advised of offense and minimum/maximum penalty.  Receipt Admitted - Reading Waived.  Advised of right of Counsel. Defendant does not wish to have counsel at this time and wishes to enter a plea. Defendant is working toward obtaining a CDL.
